I just faced almost the same issue (the app worked using my IDE but not using the generated jar file). I solved it by adding the option `&lt;Multi-Release&gt;true&lt;/Multi-Release&gt;`. This option specifies that your Uber java may contain various Java versions of Java files.

```
&lt;archive&gt;
  &lt;manifestEntries&gt;
    &lt;Multi-Release&gt;true&lt;/Multi-Release&gt;
  &lt;/manifestEntries&gt;
  &lt;manifest&gt;
    &lt;mainClass&gt;com.javacodegeeks.snippets.enterprise.App2&lt;/mainClass&gt;
  &lt;/manifest&gt;
&lt;/archive&gt;
```

See https://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-compiler-plugin/multirelease.html for more details.

